index: Building Scalable Applications in Java & Spring Masterclass
description: Building scalable applications in Java and Spring involves designing and implementing applications that can handle increasing amounts of data, traffic, and users. This requires following best practices and design principles such as loose coupling, modularization, and fault tolerance. Java and Spring provide powerful tools and frameworks for building distributed systems, monitoring performance, and optimizing resource utilization. By leveraging these tools and principles, developers can build robust, scalable applications that can adapt to changing business needs and user requirements.

description: A comprehensive chase to excel in any interview for the Data Structures and Algorithms. This course has been specifically designed to provide resources that would assist you in cracking problem-solving interviews. The presented problems in the course would suffice to look for positive outcomes in the interviews. Complete DSA (Data Structures and Algorithms) in Python is a comprehensive course that covers all the fundamental concepts, techniques, and best practices of DSA using Python programming language. You will learn different sorting algorithms such as bubble sort, selection sort, insertion sort, quicksort, and mergesort and how to implement them using Python. Additionally, you will learn how to search for elements in a data structure using binary search and linear search. The Programme features include the Course material and Lifetime dashboard access for the learner. The Course covers all the essential topics of DSA using Python programming language. It is well-designed for beginners who want to learn DSA from scratch and for professionals who want to enhance their DSA skills using Python.

index: Build Modern ETL Data Pipeline using Informatica cloud
seo: {'keywords': 'Build Modern ETL Data Pipeline using Informatica cloud'}
description: A very common use case in data engineering is to build an ETL system for a data warehouse, to have data loaded in from multiple separate databases to enable data analysts/scientists to be able to run queries on this data since the source databases are used by your applications and we do not want these analytic queries to affect our application performance and the source data. In this project, we will build an ETL system with Informatica cloud. Informatica Cloud is an on-demand subscription service that provides a complete platform for cloud integration and data management.

seo: {'keywords': 'Build ETL Data Pipeline on AWS EMR Cluster'}
description: With the advent of powerful data warehouses like SnowFlake, BigQuery, redshift spectrum, etc that allow separation of storage and execution, it has become very economical to store data in the data warehouse and then transform them as required. This Project goes over how to design such a ELT system using AWS EMR and Hive. The main objective is to keep the code complexity and server management low, while automating as much as possible

index: Create A Data Pipeline based on Messaging Using PySpark and Airflow
seo: {'keywords': ' Create A Data Pipeline based on Messaging Using PySpark and Airflow'}
description: In this Project, we will learn how to Build a Big Data pipeline on AWS at scale. You will be using the Covid-19 dataset. This will be streamed in real time from an external API using NiFi. The complex JSON data will be parsed into CSV format using NiFi and the result will be stored in HDFS. Then this data will be sent to Kafka for data processing using PySpark. The processed data will then be consumed from Spark and stored in HDFS. Then a Hive external table is created on top of HDFS. Finally the cleaned, transformed data is stored in the data lake and deployed. Visualization is then done using Tableau and AWS QuickSight.

description: The Air Pressure System (APS) is a critical component of a heavy-duty vehicle that uses compressed air to force a piston to provide pressure to the brake pads, slowing the vehicle down. The benefits of using an APS instead of a hydraulic system are the easy availability and long-term sustainability of natural air. This is a Binary Classification problem, in which the affirmative class indicates that the failure was caused by a certain component of the APS, while the negative class indicates that the failure was caused by something else.

index: The Ultimate Guide To OpenAI GPT-3 & Fine Tune with Custom Data
seo: {'keywords': 'The Ultimate Guide To OpenAI GPT-3 & Fine Tune with Custom Data'}
description: Generative Pre-trained Transformer 3 (GPT-3; stylized GPTÂ·3) is an autoregressive language model that uses deep learning to produce human-like text. Given an initial text as prompt, it will produce text that continues the prompt. The architecture is a standard transformer network (with a few engineering tweaks) with the unprecedented size of 2048-token-long context and 175 billion parameters (requiring 800 GB of storage). The training method is ""generative pretraining"", meaning that it is trained to predict what the next token is. The model demonstrated strong few-shot learning on many text-based tasks.

index: Industry Safety Detection using YOLO v7
description: The purpose of this project is to create a detection system using Computer Vision and Machine Learning to monitor, track and enforce employees/workers to wear the necessary protection gear. ISD is designed and modeled to take a real-time image of the personnel as the input and determine if the five segments - helmet, gloves, jacket, goggles, and footwear are worn before entering the workplace, and record the procedures as well. If ISD does not find any of the safety gears, the worker will not be allowed to proceed and the prohibition alarm in the system will alert the authorities

description: In this data science project, you will build a machine learning system that will be able to predict the cost of the shipment or package by using machine learning algorithms. This project will be very useful for logistics companies, where on a day-to-day basis a lot of couriers, packages, or goods are transported via different modes of transport. The main concern with these logistics companies is trying to deliver these goods in an efficient and cost-efficient way possible, so the pricing of the shipment is tricky and involves a lot of variables to consider while the pricing of the shipment. There might be scenarios where the shipment might be delayed due to some external reasons, leading to a loss for the company and a delay in delivery of the shipment. So logistics companies need to use dynamic pricing based on several factors and variables to price the shipment in such a way that there are no losses to the company and the price of the shipment is as less as possible so that customers can use their services more due to effective pricing rates.

description: The full-stack data analytics course is meant to assist you in becoming a skilled data analyst. Learn how to deal with SQL databases, develop data visualizations, and apply predictive analytics and statistics in a corporate environment using the best analytics tools and methodologies. This Full Stack Data Analytics course is designed to provide students with a comprehensive understanding of data analytics and how to use data to drive business decisions. Throughout the course, students will learn the skills necessary to collect, process, analyze, and communicate data effectively. In this course, students will be introduced to the fundamentals of data analytics, including data cleaning, exploration, and visualization. They will also learn about probability and statistics, and how to apply statistical concepts to analyze data. Students will also learn about data modeling and how to use predictive modeling techniques to forecast future trends. They will learn about regression, time-series analysis, and other statistical techniques used for data modeling. By the end of this course, students will have a strong foundation in data analytics and will be equipped with the skills and knowledge needed to work with data in a wide range of industries. They will also have a portfolio of projects to showcase their skills to potential employers.

description:
By using the tools and processes that big data scientists and engineers use on a daily basis, you will be intelligent enough to understand the insights that big data may offer. With a general understanding of how large data is arranged, examined, and evaluated, you can make better business judgments. This unique industry program will help to learn the entire stack of Big Data and be ready to crack jobs in leading organizations. This Big Data course is designed to provide students with a comprehensive understanding of big data technologies and how to process and analyze large datasets. Throughout the course, students will learn the skills necessary to work with big data, including distributed computing, data storage, and processing frameworks.

Students will be introduced to big data fundamentals, including Hadoop, Spark, and MapReduce. They will learn about the architecture and components of Hadoop, including HDFS, YARN, and MapReduce, and how to use Hadoop to process and analyze large datasets. Students will also learn about distributed computing and how to use Spark to process large datasets. They will learn about Spark's architecture, components, and APIs, and how to use Spark for data processing, machine learning, and real-time analytics.By the end of this course, students will have a strong foundation in big data technologies and be equipped with the skills and knowledge needed to work with large datasets in various industries. They will also have a portfolio of projects to showcase their skills to potential employers.

description: DevOps, which is a mix of cultural principles, practices, and technologies such as Linux foundations, Docker, Kubernetes, Ansible, Terraform, ArgoCD, AWS Cloud, Git, Git, Prometheus, and others, increases an organization's capacity to build applications and services at high velocity. Become a DevOps master and increase the velocity of production now. This comprehensive DevOps Developer Course is designed to equip students with the necessary skills and knowledge to succeed as a DevOps professional in today's fast-paced, agile development environment. The course is aimed at beginners and experienced developers who wish to learn about DevOps practices and how to implement them in their projects. Students will learn how to build, test, deploy, and manage applications using DevOps principles and tools throughout the course. They will gain hands-on experience in DevOps tools such as DevOps, Linux, Git, AWS, Docker, Ansible, Kubernetes, Terraform, CI CD Pipelines, Argo CD, Prometheus, and Grafana. The course will cover infrastructure automation, continuous integration, delivery, monitoring, and security.

index: Web Automation Using Selenium With Java and Cucumber BDD Tech Neuron
seo: {'keywords': 'Web Automation Using Selenium With Java and Cucumber BDD Tech Neuron'}
description: In this live training program, you will be learning everything about Automation using different tools and libraries. We will be starting with Java from scratch (from zero) and will be automating Web Applications and APIs as well. This course includes most of the leading tools, libraries, and frameworks TestNG, Cucumber, Maven, Git, Github, GitHub Actions, Docker, and Jenkins (CI-CD). After this course, you will be ready to attend interviews and will be able to automate different Web Applications. This live training program on Web Automation Using Selenium with Java and Cucumber BDD Tech Neuron covers the basics of Java and Automation, and then dives into Selenium 4, TestNG, Cucumber, Maven, Git, GitHub, Docker, and Jenkins (CI/CD). By the end of the course, students will be equipped with the knowledge and skills to automate web applications and API's, and will be prepared for interviews. The curriculum covers Java fundamentals, Selenium basics, intermediate and advanced topics, and additional tools and libraries such as AutoIT, headless browsers, and JavaScriptExecutor. The program also includes real-time scenarios and interview questions. Students need a system with an internet connection, an interest in learning, and dedication.

description:
This Full Stack Data Science Bootcamp 2.0 course is designed to provide students with a comprehensive understanding of the core concepts, techniques, and tools used in data science. Throughout the course, students will learn the skills to extract data insights, build predictive models, and communicate their findings effectively.
Students will be introduced to the fundamentals of data science, including data cleaning, exploration, and visualization. They will also learn about probability and statistics, and how to apply statistical concepts to analyze data. Students will learn about machine learning techniques, including supervised and unsupervised learning. They will learn how to build predictive models using regression, classification, clustering, and dimensionality reduction. By the end of this course, students will have a strong data science foundation and be equipped with the skills and knowledge needed to work with data in a wide range of industries. They will also have a portfolio of projects to showcase their skills to potential employers.

description: Dull Stack Django React Certification course makes it simple to create dynamic and interactive online apps by providing elegant answers to some of front-end programming's most vexing problems. It is quick, scalable, adaptable, and powerful, and it has a thriving development community that is expanding quickly. The time is now to become familiar with React. The Full Stack Django and React Courses are designed to equip students with the necessary skills and knowledge to develop modern web applications using the Django and React frameworks. This course will cover the essential concepts of both frameworks and provide hands-on training for building full-stack web applications. The course will begin with an introduction to Django, covering topics such as models, views, templates, forms, and authentication. Students will learn to build a fully functional backend using Django, including integrating third-party apps and APIs.Students will work on multiple projects throughout the course such as Django and Django REST framework, Django tour - quick, Django admin and migration, Storing our images in Django, Setting Django API structure, Handling API root route in Django, building full-stack web applications that integrate Django and React. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of both frameworks and be able to develop and deploy their web applications.

description: This  Backend Development with Nodejs course is designed to give students a comprehensive understanding of backend development using Nodejs. Nodejs is a powerful, versatile runtime environment allowing developers to build highly scalable and efficient web applications. In this course, students will learn the fundamentals of Nodejs and how it can be used for backend development. Topics covered in the course include creating and managing web servers, Javascript, ES6, Web servers, Express Js, Body parsers, Middlewares, View Engines, Multer, Passport JS, Big Stack, MongoDB integration with Node JS, and deploying Nodejs applications to production environments. The course will also cover popular Nodejs frameworks and libraries such as Express, MongoDB, Mongoose, and Socket. IO. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of how to build scalable and robust backend systems using Nodejs.

description:
In this course, you'll learn how to solve complex programming puzzles and implement various algorithms that you'll encounter in coding interviews. You'll explore arrays, strings, recursion, linked lists, math, stack and queue, sorting, trees, graphs, and dynamic programming. For each topic, you'll explore common interview problems and solutions and learn how to craft code that will impress your interviewer.

To get the most out of this course, you'll need a system with an internet connection, a passion for learning, and dedication to mastering algorithmic programming. We'll start with preparing for the interview, including non-tech round preparation techniques to give you an edge in your job search. You'll then explore array interview problems, including binary search, rotation of arrays, and finding triplets. You'll learn string interview problems such as word in a sentence, duplicates, and longest substring. Recursion interview problems will include Fibonacci, popular subset problems, and decimal to binary conversion. By the end of this course, you'll have mastered various algorithms and programming techniques and be fully prepared for your next coding interview.

description: Angular Crash Course is a popular web application development framework maintained by Google. This crash course is designed to introduce Angular and equip learners with the foundational knowledge required to build web applications with the framework. Participants will learn how to create reusable components, implement data binding and handle user events. The course will also cover using Angular to handle forms, perform HTTP requests, and navigate between different views in a single-page application. The Angular JS course will consist of a mix of theoretical and practical sessions. Participants will be provided with coding exercises and projects to complete to reinforce their learning. By the end of the course, learners will have built a functioning web application using Angular.

description:
To get ready for other Azure role-based certifications like Azure Database Administrator Associate or Azure Data Engineer Associate, take the DP-900: Azure Data Fundamentals exam. Candidates who are just starting to work with cloud data are the target audience for this exam.
The DP-900 Microsoft Azure Data Fundamentals course is ideal for beginners who want to work with cloud data and obtain certification in Azure Data Fundamentals. The course covers a range of topics, including data concepts, relational databases, and various Azure services such as Azure Synapse and Data Lake, Account Storage, Power BI, MS SQL Server, Azure Tables Cosmos DB, Hadoop Systems, Azure, and Databricks. Additionally, the course covers database security, ELT, and SQL tools, and provides demos to help students understand the services and tools. To enroll in this course, you need an internet-connected system, an interest in learning, and dedication. By the end of the course, students will have the skills to apply their knowledge of Azure Data Fundamentals in real-world scenarios, making it an excellent foundation for Azure role-based certifications like Azure Database Administrator Associate or Azure Data Engineer Associate.

description: This course will help you to get started with the fundamentals of Big Data in AWS Cloud and using other services for data analysis. This AWS Big Data Analytics course covers the fundamentals of Big Data in the AWS Cloud, including data collection, storage, processing, analysis, and visualization. It includes an overview of services such as Kinesis, SQS, Direct Connect, S3, DynamoDB, Lambda, and EMR. The course also covers important topics such as the difference between Hdfs and S3, Spark basics, and Redshift architecture. This course is ideal for those who want to learn about Big Data and its implementation in AWS. To take this course, you need a system with internet connectivity, an interest in learning, and dedication. The course includes hands-on exercises, practical demonstrations, and case studies to help learners gain a deeper understanding of the concepts. After completing this course, learners will be able to use AWS services effectively for Big Data analytics.

description: Data practitioners must master SQL since it is the most essential query language you can learn. Many prominent relational database management systems such as MySQL employ it. As a result, learning MySQL offers up a plethora of prospects and occupations - whether you want to work with relational databases or become a data scientist, knowing Mysql is essential. Even if you have no previous experience of MySQL, this practical course will build the groundwork for SQL and structured database querying.

description:
Full-stack data science course is a live mentor-led job guaranteed certification program with a full-time one-year internship provided by I Neuron, in this course, you will learn the entire stack required to work in the data science, data analytics, and big data domain, including machine learning, deep learning, computer vision NLP and Big data including MLOps and cloud infrastructure, along with real-time industry projects and product development with the I Neuron product development team, which will enable you to contribute on various levels. This course is designed to provide students with a comprehensive understanding of data analytics and how to use data to drive business decisions. Students will learn the skills necessary to collect, process, analyze, and communicate data effectively throughout the course.
Students will be introduced to the fundamentals of data analytics, including data cleaning, exploration, and visualization. They will also learn about probability and statistics, and how to apply statistical concepts to analyze data. In the course, students will learn about data modeling and how to use predictive modeling techniques to forecast future trends. They will learn about regression, time-series analysis, and other statistical techniques used for data modeling. By the end of this course, students will have a strong foundation in data analytics and will be equipped with the skills and knowledge needed to work with data in a wide range of industries. They will also have a portfolio of projects to showcase their skills to potential employers.

description: The most widely used Python web development framework is Django. Django is a Python framework that covers all elements of web development, from handling requests and answers to creating dynamic HTML pages using templates and making database access and maintenance simple. description:
Explore how the world of data has evolved and how the advent of cloud technologies is providing new opportunities for businesses to explore. You will learn the various data platform technologies that are available, and how a Data Engineer can take advantage of this technology to an organization's benefit.Join our Azure Data Engineering course to explore the exciting world of data engineering and discover how cloud technologies, particularly Microsoft Azure, can help organizations unlock the full potential of their data. This course will cover the responsibilities of a data engineer and their relationship with other data and AI professionals, common data engineering practices, and a high-level architecting process for data engineering projects.

You'll learn about cloud computing, the different cloud models, and the unique features of various cloud providers. We'll dive deeper into Azure and discuss Regions and Availability Zones, creating a Microsoft Azure account, and the significance of the Resource Hierarchy. We'll also cover Resource groups, subscription and management groups, and Azure Active Directory. Finally, we'll introduce Azure cloud computing, managed and unmanaged services, and give you hands-on experience creating an Azure SQL database service. All you need is a system with an internet connection, dedication, and an interest to learn. By the end of this course, you'll have the skills and knowledge necessary to take advantage of Azure technology and help organizations benefit from their data. Get ready to explore the world of Azure Data Engineering!

description: In this Oracle 11g PL/SQL course you will receive introduction training on PL/SQL database programming language covering syntax, structure and features of the language within the context of database applications and programming.Join our Oracle 11g PL/SQL course to receive introduction training on PL/SQL database programming language, covering its syntax, structure, and features in the context of database applications and programming. The course requires a system with at least an i3 processor and 4GB RAM, a working internet connection, and dedication to learning. Basic SQL knowledge is beneficial but not required. Our curriculum covers installation, basic syntax, data types, variables, literals, operators, conditions, loops, strings, arrays, procedures, functions, cursors, records, exceptions, triggers, packages, collections, transactions, and DBMS output. By the end of the course, you will have a strong foundation in PL/SQL programming language and be able to create complex database applications. Enhance your skills in PL/SQL and join us on this exciting learning journey.

description: In this hands-on course, You will learn how to filter, change, and edit images. You will also learn how to use OpenCV to perform various image processing tasks with hands-on practical experience. Students who complete this course will be able to apply what they have learned in this course to a variety of fields, including machine learning and artificial intelligence, machine and robotic vision, space and medical image analysis, and many more. Join the hands-on Image Processing course to learn how to filter, edit, and change images using OpenCV. This course is perfect for those interested in machine learning, artificial intelligence, robotic vision, space and medical image analysis, and more. You will gain practical experience and work on projects that apply the skills you learned. The course requires an internet connection, interest in learning, and dedication. The course covers image processing fundamentals, color spaces, creating basic drawings, and advanced OpenCV techniques. You will also learn about different image formats, compression, and pixel definitions. In addition, you will explore different color spaces such as RGB, XYZ, HSV/HSL, and LAB color space. Finally, the course introduces Scikit image and covers how to upload, view, and save images, get resolution, and convert color spaces. By completing this course, you will have gained practical experience in image processing using OpenCV and can apply your skills to various fields.

description:
Google Cloud Platform is one of the most used cloud platforms across the globe that work on the same infrastructure that Google uses internally for its end-user products such as - Google Search, Gmail, Google Drive, and YouTube. In addition, we can use these services in different stacks like Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Big Data, etc. This course gives you a detailed understanding of GCP from essential to advanced, which helps you get various opportunities. Our comprehensive course on Google Cloud Platform (GCP) provides a thorough understanding of one of the most widely used cloud platforms in the world. GCP is built on the same infrastructure that powers Google's own products, like Google Search, Gmail, Google Drive, and YouTube. In this course, you'll learn about Compute Service, App Engine, Cloud Storage, Google Cloud Billing, and Cloud Pricing. We'll also cover IAM (Identity and Access Management), critical for maintaining security and access control within GCP. No prior knowledge of any programming language is required for this course. All you need is a system with an internet connection and dedication to learning. The course curriculum is designed to be easy to follow and engaging, starting with an introduction to cloud computing and GCP, then progressing to more advanced topics, including GCP cloud services for Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and Natural Language Processing.

By the end of the course, you'll have the knowledge and skills needed to confidently work with GCP and its various products and services. Whether you're interested in pursuing a career in cloud computing or simply want to learn more about this fascinating technology, this course is an excellent place to start.

seo: {'keywords': 'DSA course online, competitive programming courses, competitive programming, DSA Certification Course, DSA courses Online'}
description: This course on Data Structures and Algorithms with Competitive Programming is designed for beginners to advance in Python language. The entire course will cover topics such as analysis of algorithms, divide and conquer, greedy techniques, dynamic programming, arrays, linked lists, skip lists, hashing, trees, graph traversal, stack, queue, string matching, NP-Hard and NP-Complete problems, and much more. You'll learn about asymptotic notation, including big O, omega, and theta, and how to solve recurrence relations. We'll explore divide and conquer techniques, greedy techniques, and dynamic programming. You'll also learn about arrays, searching and sorting techniques. To take this course, you'll need dedication and a PC with internet connectivity. By the end of this course, you'll have a solid understanding of data structures and algorithms and be able to apply them to solve real-world problems.
